      %h2.article-main-title Arthritis
      .article-main-content
        %p The term arthritis refers to a group of conditions that involve inflammation in one or more joints in the body and the result is invariably pain. Arthritis can come in many forms and currently there are over 100 different kinds - the most common of which is osteoarthritis. Typically, people will experience a constant, localized pain in the affected joint, along with stiffness, swelling and a chronic aching that gets worse with activity.




